  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study aims to assess usual walking speed (4-metre gait speed) in patients undergoing
      primary percutaneous coronary intervention (PCI) for acute myocardial infarction and to
      assess whether this can predict future cardiovascular events and death.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
